# RFC-0009 Agent Marketplace Discovery

Status: Accepted

## Abstract

Agent Marketplace Discovery defines a standardized framework for discovering, evaluating, advertising, and consuming autonomous agents within the APP ecosystem.

The marketplace layer enables organizations, individuals, and agents to locate trusted capabilities across federated networks.

This RFC establishes the foundation for an interoperable agent economy.

---

# Motivation

As the number of autonomous systems grows, users require mechanisms to discover:

* Service agents
* Research agents
* Compliance agents
* Finance agents
* Procurement agents
* Industry-specific agents

Without a common discovery framework, ecosystems become fragmented and vendor-specific.

APP provides a common marketplace discovery layer.

---

# Design Goals

The marketplace should enable:

* Discovery
* Trust
* Verification
* Federation
* Interoperability

without requiring central ownership.

---

# Marketplace Model

APP does not define a centralized marketplace.

Instead, APP defines a federated marketplace protocol.

Any organization may:

* Publish agents
* Operate directories
* Provide discovery services
* Offer marketplace experiences

---

