# Trust Requirements

Discovery systems SHOULD surface:

* Passport Status
* Reputation
* Federation Participation
* Attestations
* Ownership History

Trust information should be visible before engagement.

---

# Capability Verification

Marketplace operators may verify agent capabilities.

Verification may include:

* Testing
* Audits
* Attestations
* Federation Reviews

Verified capabilities should be distinguishable from self-declared capabilities.

---

# Marketplace Reputation

Reputation may be influenced by:

* Successful interactions
* Authority Attestations
* Federation Standing
* Operational History

Consumers should be able to understand why an agent is trusted.

---

# Agent Commerce

Future marketplace implementations may support:

* Usage-Based Billing
* Subscription Models
* Revenue Sharing
* Capability Licensing
* Agent-to-Agent Payments

APP provides the trust layer, not the payment layer.

---

# Federation Discovery

Discovery may occur across federation boundaries.

Organizations may search:

```text
Local Node
    ↓
Federated Nodes
    ↓
Authority Directories
```

This enables a global agent discovery network.

---

# Marketplace Endorsements

Organizations may endorse agents.

Examples:

* Verified Vendor
* Certified Partner
* Trusted Research Provider
* Enterprise Approved

These endorsements may be expressed through APP Attestations.

---

# Future Vision

The long-term vision is an open agent economy where:

* Agents discover other agents
* Agents negotiate with agents
* Agents purchase services from agents
* Agents delegate work to agents

while trust remains verifiable and portable.

---

# Security Considerations

Marketplace discovery systems should guard against:

* Impersonation
* Reputation manipulation
* Sybil attacks
* Fraudulent attestations
* Fake capabilities

Trust signals should be evidence-based and cryptographically verifiable.

---

# Conclusion

Agent Marketplace Discovery establishes the discovery layer of the emerging agent economy and enables trusted interaction between autonomous systems at global scale.
